            <title>[JDK-8327840] Automate javax/swing/border/Test4129681.java</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8327840</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>The javax/swing/border/Test4129681.java test has a potential to be automatic test.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The test verifies whether the title in a titled border associated with a disabled component renders using disabled colors.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
If you render JLabel into a BufferedImage or take a screenshot, you can analyse the color of the pixels, especially if you turn off text antialising.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Instead of real text, you can use a full block character: &amp;quot;&#9608;&amp;quot; (U+2588) which will make analysing the pixel colors more robust.</description>
